-- Verizon Wireless Drops Plan for $2 Fee for Single Payments
-- B y   J e r a n   W i t t e n s t e i n
-- 2011-12-30T20:29:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-30/verizon-wireless-decides-to-abandon-2-single-payment-fee-after-protests.html
Verizon Wireless, the largest U.S. 
mobile carrier, said it has dropped plans to charge customers 
a $2 fee for online or telephone single payments.  Verizon, which announced the plan earlier this week, made
the decision in response to customer feedback, the company said
in a statement on its website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeran Wittenstein at 
 jwittenstei1@bloomberg.net  